</span></span><span class="btn-text">Shop Recipe</span></a>		<div class="ad-container-wrapper  ad-type-content glide-on-mobile recipe-after-ingredients-ad">
			<div id="RecipeCard-ShopButton" class="tmbi-ad-slot ay-ad-unit-wrapper " data-slot="RecipeCard_ShopButton" data-ad-unit-path="/6178/toh_mobile/detail/RecipeCard_ShopButton" data-targeting="{&#34;pos&#34;:&#34;content&#34;,&#34;theme&#34;:&#34;basic&#34;,&#34;DAI&#34;:&#34;n&#34;}" data-is-sticky="0" data-is-out-of-page="0" data-glide-on-mobile="1" data-glide-on-desktop="0">
	</div>
			</div>
		</div><div class="recipe-directions">
	<h3 class="directions-title">Directions</h3>
	<ol class="directions-list">
					<li class="direction-step">Place cloves, peppercorns and bay leaf on a double thickness of cheesecloth; bring up corners of cloth and tie with kitchen string to form a bag. In a large bowl, combine the water, vinegar, sugar, salt and ginger. Add beef and spice bag; let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.</li>
					<div class="ad-container-wrapper  ad-type-content glide-on-mobile">
			<div id="RecipeCard-direction1" class="tmbi-ad-slot ay-ad-unit-wrapper " data-slot="RecipeCard_direction1" data-ad-unit-path="/6178/toh_mobile/detail/RecipeCard_direction1" data-targeting="{&#34;pos&#34;:&#34;content&#34;,&#34;theme&#34;:&#34;basic&#34;,&#34;DAI&#34;:&#34;n&#34;}" data-is-sticky="0" data-is-out-of-page="0" data-glide-on-mobile="1" data-glide-on-desktop="0">
	</div>
			</div>
		
					<li class="direction-step">   Transfer all to a 6-qt. electric pressure cooker. Add carrots, celery and onion. Lock the lid and close pressure-release valve. Adjust to pressure-cook on high for 10 minutes. Quick-release pressure. Select saute setting and adjust for medium heat; bring liquid to a boil. Discard the spice bag. Stir in gingersnaps; cook and stir until thickened, about 3 minutes. Serve with egg noodles. If desired, top with parsley and pepper.</li>
			
			</ol>
</div>
	</div>
	<div class="recipe-card-footer">
		<div class="nutrition-facts-wrap">
	<h3 class="nf-title">Nutrition Facts</h3>
	<div class="nf-content">
		1 cup: 228 calories, 5g fat (2g saturated fat), 63mg cholesterol, 436mg sodium, 18g carbohydrate (8g sugars, 2g fiber), 27g protein. <b><b>Diabetic Exchanges</b>: </b> 3 lean meat, 1 starch, 1 vegetable.	</div>
